# @ui Component Conventions

## Imports

- Use `@ui` / `@ui/*` for primitives (Button, TextField, Dialog, List, etc.)
- Use `@icons/svg/{Name}.svg` for SVG icons (import each icon separately)
- Do **not** import from `@mui/*` or `@emotion/*`

## Styling

- Use CSS Modules (`.module.css`) colocated with components
- Use design tokens from `src/css/colors.css` via CSS variables (`var(--primary-color)`, etc.)
- Do **not** use MUI `sx` props — use `className`, `style`, or module classes
- Shared dialog layout patterns live in `src/css/dialog-patterns.module.css`

## Architecture

- **Views** (`src/views/`) import **widgets** (`@widgets/*`) for app-aware components
- **Widgets** (`src/components/Widgets/`) wrap `@ui` primitives with business logic, validation, and app styling
- Use `@ui` directly in views only when no widget exists and the primitive is sufficient

## Icons

- Source SVGs live in `src/components/Icons/svg/{Name}.svg`
- Icons are compiled at build time via SVGR — no codegen step
- To add a new icon:
  1. Add `src/components/Icons/svg/NewIcon.svg` (e.g. from [Google Material Icons](https://fonts.google.com/icons))
  2. `import NewIcon from "@icons/svg/NewIcon.svg"` in code

## TextField props

Use explicit props, not legacy MUI `slotProps`:

- `inputClassName`, `selectClassName`
- `startAdornment`, `endAdornment`
- `inputProps`, `selectProps`

## List navigation

- Use `ListItemButton` with `component={Link}` and `href` for hash-routed sidebar links
- `List` accepts `component` prop (default `"ul"`)
